 wxyz = (w+x+y+z)^2 \tag{1}
a,b,c,d
 a+b+c+d = 2s = w+x+y+z 
 w = s-a, x = s-b, y = s-c, z = s-d 
 w \ge x \ge y \ge z, \; \; \; xyz \ge 2(w+x+y+z) 
p,t
w \le t
p \ge 2(w+t)
(1)
wp=(w+t)^2.\tag{1}
w
wp \ge 2w^2+2wt.
(1)
x+y+z \ge w
(w+t)^2 \ge 2w^2+2wt, \\ w^2+2wt+t^2 \ge 2w^2+2wt, \\ w^2 \le t^2, \\ w \le t 
